    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush and Gore, on the Battleground of Ideas</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David G Paul letter on Sept 6 article scores George W Bush's Medicare plan, holding insurers will not compete to provide coverage to elderly</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Bush Spells Out Major Overhaul in Medicare Plan'' (front page, Sept. 6):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Bush Spells Out Major Overhaul in Medicare Plan'' (front page, Sept. 6):</p>
        <p>The idea of insurance companies competing to provide health coverage for the elderly is ludicrous. Anyone will tell you that insurers do what they can to avoid selling policies to those folks who are the most likely to file claims for benefits. Do you know any young male drivers who are inundated by offers to buy auto insurance?</p>
        <p>When it comes to health insurance for the elderly, there was never a vigorous free market of buyers and sellers, which is why Medicare was established in the first place.</p>
        <p>DAVID G. PAUL  Lambertville, N.J., Sept. 6, 2000</p>
      </block>
